<p>as black as the coal and we could only recognise one another by their voice.<br/>During this shift they called for five volunteers to go into the Bordas bunkers to relieve the firemen in clearing the shoots, as we had been sending the coal down so quick that they got chocked.<br/>John and I volunteered, and when we got down below the dust was so thick that we could hardly see our hand</p>
